.TH "spi_nor_find_best_erase_type" 9 "spi_nor_find_best_erase_type" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_nor_find_best_erase_type \- find the best erase type for the given offset in the serial flash memory and the number of bytes to erase. The region in which the address fits is expected to be provided.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct spi_nor_erase_type *" spi_nor_find_best_erase_type
.BI "(const struct spi_nor_erase_map *map "  ","
.BI "const struct spi_nor_erase_region *region "  ","
.BI "u64 addr "  ","
.BI "u32 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map" 12
the erase map of the SPI NOR
.IP "region" 12
pointer to a structure that describes a SPI NOR erase region
.IP "addr" 12
offset in the serial flash memory
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to erase
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the best fitted erase type, NULL otherwise.
